'''Backgrounding''' is an intermediate stage sometimes used in [[cattle]] production which begins after [[weaning]] and ends upon placement in a [[feedlot]].  Background feeding relies more heavily on [[forage]] (e.g., [[pasture]], [[hay]]) in combination with [[Cereal|grains]] to increase a [[calf]]’s weight by several hundred pounds and to build up immunity to diseases before it enters a feedlot. Some cattle operations specialize in backgrounding. 

